# SEO Rules

Build for useful programmatic SEO, not thin-page spam.

Do not create infinite indexed value-only pages such as:
- /5-acres-to-square-feet/
- /6-acres-to-square-feet/
- /7-acres-to-square-feet/

Use canonical converter pages instead:
- /unit-converters/area/acres-to-square-feet/
- /unit-converters/area/square-feet-to-acres/

Value-specific inputs may be handled with query parameters or form state, but canonical URLs should point to the main tool page unless the page has materially unique content.

Each indexed tool page must provide distinct utility, examples, assumptions, source notes, or workflow-specific guidance.

Every public tool page should have:
- unique title
- unique meta description
- canonical URL
- Open Graph metadata
- breadcrumb data
- related internal links
- schema markup where appropriate
- sitemap inclusion when published and indexable

Do not overuse FAQ or HowTo schema as a gimmick.

Prioritize:
- SoftwareApplication schema for tools
- BreadcrumbList schema for navigation
- WebPage metadata
- clear internal linking

Use docs/05-seo-programmatic-pages.md as the detailed reference.
